    "title": "Search for Chelator Information for Particular chelator Entity in RDCdb",
    "content": "<p>Search for Chelator Information for Particular chelator Entity\nin RDCdb</p>\n<p>n the “RDC Search” section, users can search the full-text content of\nthe RDCdb database to identify relevant RDC entries by entering keywords\nsuch as RDC drug names, target names, ligand names, linker names,\nradionuclide names, chelator names, and other related terms.</p>\n<p>To perform a search, users simply enter a keyword in the main search\nbox and submit the query. The search results page will display\ncomprehensive information on all RDC drugs directly associated with the\nsearch term, including the RDC name, drug development stage, drug\ntype, ligand name, linker name, chelator name, radionuclide name, and\ndetailed links to the corresponding target information.</p>\n<p>In order to facilitate a more customized input query, the wild\ncharacters of \"?\" are also supported.</p>\n<p>(1) If search \"DOTA-MAL\", find a single API entry which is\nnamed \"DOTA-MAL\";</p>\n<p>(2)If search \"DOTA\", finds a series entries with chelator\nnames.</p>\n<p><img src=\"/manual/Manual-5-chelator_media/media/image1.png\"\nstyle=\"width:5.76528in;height:2.85903in\" /></p>\n<p>Using DOTA as an example, the “General Information of This Chelator”\nsection presents the basic information of the chelator, including its\nchelator ID, name, synonyms, external links, chemical structure,\nmolecular formula, SMILES, InChI, InChIKey, IUPAC name, physicochemical\nproperties, and ligand type. Please note that the physicochemical\nproperties are calculated using the RDKit tool.</p>\n<p><img src=\"/manual/Manual-5-chelator_media/media/image2.png\"\nstyle=\"width:5.76806in;height:8.52014in\" /></p>\n<p>The \"Related RDCs\" section is about Each Radionuclide Conjugate\nRelated to This Chelator, which displays the radionuclide drug\nconjugates (RDCs) associated with this chelator. Clicking each button\nwill redirect users to the corresponding detail page for that\nradionuclide drug conjugate (RDC).</p>\n<p><img src=\"/manual/Manual-5-chelator_media/media/image3.png\"\nstyle=\"width:5.76806in;height:3.51528in\" /></p>"
