    "title": "Search for Radionuclide Information for Particular radionuclide Entity in RDCdb",
    "content": "<p>Search for Radionuclide Information for Particular radionuclide\nEntity in RDCdb</p>\n<p>n the “RDC Search” section, users can search the full-text content of\nthe RDCdb database to identify relevant RDC entries by entering keywords\nsuch as RDC drug names, target names, ligand names, linker names,\nradionuclide names, chelator names, and other related terms.</p>\n<p>To perform a search, users simply enter a keyword in the main search\nbox and submit the query. The search results page will display\ncomprehensive information on all RDC drugs directly associated with the\nsearch term, including the RDC name, drug development stage, drug type,\nligand name, linker name, chelator name, radionuclide name, and detailed\nlinks to the corresponding target information.</p>\n<p>In order to facilitate a more customized input query, the wild\ncharacters of \"?\" are also supported.</p>\n<p>(1) If search \"68Ga\", find a single API entry which is named\n\"68Ga\";</p>\n<p>(2)If search \"68\", find a single API entry which is named \"68Ga”.</p>\n<p>(3)If search “Ga” or “Gallium”,find a single API entry which is named\n\"68Ga”.</p>\n<p><img src=\"/manual/Manual-6-radionuclide_media/media/image1.png\"\nstyle=\"width:5.76597in;height:2.88681in\" /></p>\n<p>Using Gallium-68 as an example, the “General Information of This\nRadionuclide” section presents the basic information of the\nRadionuclide, including its Radionuclide ID, name, synonyms,\nRadionuclide_half_life, Radionuclide-emission, Radionuclide_energy.</p>\n<p><img src=\"/manual/Manual-6-radionuclide_media/media/image2.png\"\nstyle=\"width:5.76597in;height:2.57778in\" /></p>\n<p>The \"Related RDCs\" section is about Each Radionuclide Conjugate\nRelated to This Radionuclide, which displays the radionuclide drug\nconjugates (RDCs) associated with this Radionuclide. Clicking each\nbutton will redirect users to the corresponding detail page for that\nradionuclide drug conjugate (RDC).</p>\n<p><img src=\"/manual/Manual-6-radionuclide_media/media/image3.png\"\nstyle=\"width:5.76528in;height:3.5375in\" /></p>\n<p>The \"Complete List of RDCs Associated with This Radionuclide\" section\nsystematically displays the RDCs bound to this ligand. The list presents\ndifferent types of RDCs along with their structural component\ninformation. Users can browse the different RDCs as a whole or click the\nRDC information to quickly navigate to the corresponding RDC activity\npage.</p>\n<p><img src=\"/manual/Manual-6-radionuclide_media/media/image4.png\"\nstyle=\"width:5.76597in;height:3.49861in\" /></p>"
